## V5

This version keeps the quantitative model and charts intact while improving accessibility, removing technical file-path controls from the main sidebar, expanding 48-team display controls where available, and hardening the best-third combinations chart.

# WC2026 localhost quantitative dashboard — V4 publication layer

This project packages a fully local World Cup 2026 simulation workbench.

Core principles:
- no backend logic change relative to the working simulation project
- no chart style change relative to the existing dashboard
- additive publication layer only
- bilingual interface (English / Français)
- clearer quantitative wording without removing technical terms
- explicit model-vs-market comparison page
- explicit publication / LinkedIn-ready framing page

## What is included
- tournament simulation CLI
- pairwise Monte Carlo CLI
- best-third qualification mapping export
- Streamlit dashboard
- EN / FR interface dictionaries
- glossary docs
- publication docs
- sample market odds CSV for model-vs-market comparison

## What is not included
- no betting automation
- no wagering instruction module
- no guarantee logic
- no change to the underlying simulation engine

## Local setup

```bash
python3 -m venv .venv
source .venv/bin/activate
python -m pip install --upgrade pip
pip install -r requirements.txt
pip install -e .
```

## Validate and generate outputs

```bash
python -m wc2026.cli validate-data
python -m wc2026.cli export-third-place-map --out outputs/generated_third_place_mapping.csv
pytest -q
python -m wc2026.cli simulate-tournament --iterations 100000 --seed 20260404 --out-dir outputs/tournament_run
python -m wc2026.cli precompute-pairwise --iterations 1000000 --jobs 8 --batch-size 50000 --seed 20260404 --out outputs/pairwise_summary.csv
```

## Launch dashboard

```bash
streamlit run app.py
```

## Dashboard pages
- Overview
- Groups
- Tournament states
- Pairwise
- Team
- Model vs market
- Publication layer
- Audit

## Optional market data
The dashboard reads `data/market_odds_sample.csv` by default.

Expected columns:
- `team`
- `title_american`
- optional metadata columns such as `source`, `date_utc`

